{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_15","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' /Users/danielmatthews-ferrero/Documents/local-codebases/temple-sanhedrin/research/2026-04-12-q32-intermediate-precision.md; echo '---'; sed -n '1,260p' /Users/danielmatthews-ferrero/Documents/local-codebases/temple-sanhedrin/research/2026-04-15-iq-154-wrapper-churn.md; echo '--- q8 avx2 ---'; sed -n '1,320p' src/quant/q8_0_avx2.HC; echo '--- tests avx2 ---'; ls -la tests | sed -n '1,200p'; rg -n \\\"q8_0_avx2|Q8_0MulI16LanesToI32PairsAVX2|Q8_0DotI16LanesAVX2\\\" tests src/quant\"","aggregated_output":"# Research Directive: Q32 Intermediate Precision for Accumulator Path\n\n## Trigger\nThe inference engine uses Q16 (16-bit fixed-point) for all math. When chaining through 22+ transformer layers, each layer's ~1% error compounds to ~24% drift. The accumulator path in matmul and attention needs wider precision.\n\n## Research Required\nThe Sanhedrin MUST research and document:\n\n1. **GGML's actual accumulator width** — what does llama.cpp use for intermediate sums in quantized dot products? (Hint: it uses 32-bit integer accumulators for Q4_0/Q8_0 dot products)\n\n2. **Q32 fixed-point design** — define a Q16.16 or Q8.24 format for intermediate tensor values. The final output per layer can be downscaled back to Q16, but matmul inner loops and attention score accumulation should stay Q32.\n\n3. **Where to widen** — identify the exact code paths in the inference engine that need Q32:\n   - `Q4_0DotProductBlocksQ32` accumulator (src/quant/q4_0_dot.HC)\n   - `Q8_0DotProductBlocksQ32` accumulator (src/quant/q8_0_dot.HC)\n   - Matmul output accumulation (WS4, not yet built)\n   - Attention score computation before softmax (WS5-02)\n   - RMSNorm variance accumulation (src/math/rmsnorm.HC)\n\n4. **Overflow analysis** — for a 4096-dim dot product with Q32 accumulator, what's the max possible value? Does it fit in I64? (4096 * 127 * 127 * 65536 = ~4.2e15, fits in I64 which holds 9.2e18)\n\n## Action\nWrite findings to this file. The inference agent reads Sanhedrin research/ directory each iteration.\n---\n# IQ-154 repetition research (GGUF helper churn)\n\nTrigger: `inference` repeated `IQ-154` three times with wrapper-level deltas.\n\nFindings:\n- GGUF tensor metadata already defines a canonical tensor offset field and alignment rules (`general.alignment`, default 32).\n- Repeated `ExDefaultAt` variants suggest API-surface churn rather than new behavior.\n- Better pattern: keep one checked core (`...CheckedAtEx`) and only one thin default shim; avoid stacking additional default wrappers.\n- For each new helper, require a distinct invariant (bounds, overflow, signedness, alignment) plus a parity test proving new behavior.\n\nAction for inference agent:\n- Prefer extending the checked core helper over adding another wrapper name.\n- Reject wrapper-only tasks unless tests demonstrate a new invariant.\n\nReference:\n- https://github.com/ggml-org/llama.cpp/blob/master/ggml/include/gguf.h\n--- q8 avx2 ---\n// q8_0_avx2.HC\n// AVX2-preparatory lane packing helpers for Q8_0 kernels.\n//\n// Why this exists:\n// - Upcoming tiled AVX2 matmul kernels need signed 8-bit quant lanes widened to\n//   signed 16-bit lanes before pairwise multiply-accumulate.\n// - This helper defines the exact widening contract in auditable HolyC first.\n// - Hot loops can later replace the scalar widening body with AVX2 asm\n//   (`vpmovsxbw`) without changing call-site semantics.\n\n#define Q8_0_AVX2_VALUES_PER_BLOCK   32\n#define Q8_0_AVX2_PAIR_COUNT         16\n\n#define Q8_0_AVX2_OK                 0\n#define Q8_0_AVX2_ERR_NULL_PTR       1\n#define Q8_0_AVX2_ERR_BAD_LEN        2\n#define Q8_0_AVX2_ERR_OVERFLOW       3\n\n#define Q8_0_AVX2_I64_MAX            0x7FFFFFFFFFFFFFFF\n#define Q8_0_AVX2_I64_MIN            (-0x7FFFFFFFFFFFFFFF - 1)\n\nclass Q8_0Block\n{\n    U16 d_fp16;\n    I8 qs[Q8_0_AVX2_VALUES_PER_BLOCK];\n};\n\nI32 Q8_0Pack32ToI16LanesAVX2(I8 *src_q8, I64 src_len, I16 *dst_i16, I64 dst_len)\n{\n    I64 lane;\n\n    if (!src_q8 || !dst_i16)\n        return Q8_0_AVX2_ERR_NULL_PTR;\n\n    if (src_len < Q8_0_AVX2_VALUES_PER_BLOCK)\n        return Q8_0_AVX2_ERR_BAD_LEN;\n    if (dst_len < Q8_0_AVX2_VALUES_PER_BLOCK)\n        return Q8_0_AVX2_ERR_BAD_LEN;\n\n    // Lane contract:\n    //   dst_i16[i] = SignExtend16(src_q8[i]) for i in [0, 31]\n    // This exact order matches the two AVX2 16-lane halves that would be\n    // produced by widening bytes 0..15 then 16..31.\n    for (lane = 0; lane < Q8_0_AVX2_VALUES_PER_BLOCK; ++lane)\n        dst_i16[lane] = (I16)src_q8[lane];\n\n    return Q8_0_AVX2_OK;\n}\n\nI32 Q8_0PackBlockToI16LanesAVX2(Q8_0Block *block, I16 *dst_i16, I64 dst_len)\n{\n    if (!block || !dst_i16)\n        return Q8_0_AVX2_ERR_NULL_PTR;\n\n    return Q8_0Pack32ToI16LanesAVX2(block->qs,\n                                    Q8_0_AVX2_VALUES_PER_BLOCK,\n                                    dst_i16,\n                                    dst_len);\n}\n\nI32 Q8_0MulI16LanesToI32PairsAVX2(I16 *lhs_i16,\n                                  I64 lhs_len,\n                                  I16 *rhs_i16,\n                                  I64 rhs_len,\n                                  I32 *dst_i32,\n                                  I64 dst_len)\n{\n    I64 pair_index;\n    I64 lane_base;\n    I32 product0;\n    I32 product1;\n\n    if (!lhs_i16 || !rhs_i16 || !dst_i32)\n        return Q8_0_AVX2_ERR_NULL_PTR;\n\n    if (lhs_len < Q8_0_AVX2_VALUES_PER_BLOCK)\n        return Q8_0_AVX2_ERR_BAD_LEN;\n    if (rhs_len < Q8_0_AVX2_VALUES_PER_BLOCK)\n        return Q8_0_AVX2_ERR_BAD_LEN;\n    if (dst_len < Q8_0_AVX2_PAIR_COUNT)\n        return Q8_0_AVX2_ERR_BAD_LEN;\n\n    // Contract mirrors AVX2 `vpmaddwd` lane behavior used by quantized dot kernels:\n    // - Multiply lane pairs independently in signed 16-bit domain.\n    // - Accumulate each adjacent pair into one signed 32-bit output.\n    // - Preserve lane order so output pair k maps to input lanes [2k, 2k+1].\n    for (pair_index = 0; pair_index < Q8_0_AVX2_PAIR_COUNT; ++pair_index)\n    {\n        lane_base = pair_index << 1;\n\n        product0 = lhs_i16[lane_base] * rhs_i16[lane_base];\n        product1 = lhs_i16[lane_base + 1] * rhs_i16[lane_base + 1];\n\n        dst_i32[pair_index] = product0 + product1;\n    }\n\n    return Q8_0_AVX2_OK;\n}\n\nI32 Q8_0HSumI32PairsAVX2(I32 *pairs_i32,\n                         I64 pairs_len,\n                         I64 *out_sum_i64)\n{\n    I64 pair_index;\n    I64 running_sum;\n    I64 term;\n\n    if (!pairs_i32 || !out_sum_i64)\n        return Q8_0_AVX2_ERR_NULL_PTR;\n    if (pairs_len < Q8_0_AVX2_PAIR_COUNT)\n        return Q8_0_AVX2_ERR_BAD_LEN;\n\n    // Horizontal reduction contract:\n    // - Sum all 16 pairwise I32 partial products into one signed I64 scalar.\n    // - Preserve deterministic lane order (0..15) for auditability parity\n    //   against the scalar reference path.\n    // - Explicit overflow checks keep reduction safe if this helper is reused\n    //   for wider accumulation streams in future kernels.\n    running_sum = 0;\n    for (pair_index = 0; pair_index < Q8_0_AVX2_PAIR_COUNT; ++pair_index)\n    {\n        term = (I64)pairs_i32[pair_index];\n\n        if (term > 0 && running_sum > Q8_0_AVX2_I64_MAX - term)\n            return Q8_0_AVX2_ERR_OVERFLOW;\n        if (term < 0 && running_sum < Q8_0_AVX2_I64_MIN - term)\n            return Q8_0_AVX2_ERR_OVERFLOW;\n\n        running_sum += term;\n    }\n\n    *out_sum_i64 = running_sum;\n    return Q8_0_AVX2_OK;\n}\n--- tests avx2 ---\ntotal 784\ndrwxr-xr-x  22 danielmatthews-ferrero  staff     704 Apr 16 13:30 .\ndrwxr-xr-x   9 danielmatthews-ferrero  staff     288 Apr 16 10:10 ..\ndrwxr-xr-x   6 danielmatthews-ferrero  staff     192 Apr 16 12:37 __pycache__\n-rw-r--r--   1 danielmatthews-ferrero  staff    5483 Apr 16 10:01 test_fixedpoint_q16.py\n-rw-r--r--   1 danielmatthews-ferrero  staff   12095 Apr 15 16:33 test_gguf_metadata_parse.py\n-rw-r--r--   1 danielmatthews-ferrero  staff  198841 Apr 15 21:06 test_gguf_tensor_data_base.py\n-rw-r--r--   1 danielmatthews-ferrero  staff    5050 Apr 15 16:33 test_gguf_tensorinfo_parse.py\n-rw-r--r--   1 danielmatthews-ferrero  staff    7934 Apr 15 21:32 test_intlog_q16.py\n-rw-r--r--   1 danielmatthews-ferrero  staff    7686 Apr 15 21:51 test_intlog_ratio_q16.py\n-rw-r--r--   1 danielmatthews-ferrero  staff    5196 Apr 15 16:33 test_q4_0_dequant.py\n-rw-r--r--   1 danielmatthews-ferrero  staff   13580 Apr 16 10:08 test_q4_0_dot.py\n-rw-r--r--   1 danielmatthews-ferrero  staff   23766 Apr 16 10:27 test_q4_0_q8_0_dot_kernel.py\n-rw-r--r--   1 danielmatthews-ferrero  staff   13330 Apr 16 13:08 test_q4_0_q8_0_matmul_tiled_checked.py\n-rw-r--r--   1 danielmatthews-ferrero  staff    2601 Apr 16 13:30 test_q8_0_avx2_hsum_pairs.py\n-rw-r--r--   1 danielmatthews-ferrero  staff    2914 Apr 16 13:24 test_q8_0_avx2_mul_pairs.py\n-rw-r--r--   1 danielmatthews-ferrero  staff    2975 Apr 16 13:16 test_q8_0_avx2_pack.py\n-rw-r--r--   1 danielmatthews-ferrero  staff    4719 Apr 15 16:33 test_q8_0_dequant.py\n-rw-r--r--   1 danielmatthews-ferrero  staff   28845 Apr 16 12:37 test_q8_0_dot.py\n-rw-r--r--   1 danielmatthews-ferrero  staff    5871 Apr 16 09:52 test_q8_0_dot_matrix_vector.py\n-rw-r--r--   1 danielmatthews-ferrero  staff    5676 Apr 16 12:47 test_q8_0_dot_matrix_vector_checked.py\n-rw-r--r--   1 danielmatthews-ferrero  staff   10563 Apr 16 12:55 test_q8_0_matmul_tiled_checked.py\n-rw-r--r--   1 danielmatthews-ferrero  staff    4811 Apr 15 21:44 test_softmax_entropy_q16.py\nsrc/quant/q8_0_avx2.HC:1:// q8_0_avx2.HC\nsrc/quant/q8_0_avx2.HC:61:I32 Q8_0MulI16LanesToI32PairsAVX2(I16 *lhs_i16,\ntests/test_q8_0_avx2_hsum_pairs.py:99:    print(\"q8_0_avx2_hsum_pairs_reference_checks=ok\")\ntests/test_q8_0_avx2_pack.py:122:    print(\"q8_0_avx2_pack_reference_checks=ok\")\ntests/test_q8_0_avx2_mul_pairs.py:114:    print(\"q8_0_avx2_mul_pairs_reference_checks=ok\")\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
